# --- Client (build-time, baked into the SPA bundle) ---
# Vite exposes everything prefixed VITE_* to the browser. In dev, the SDK
# points at this Worker (which proxies /api/auth/* to your Flarelink auth
# Worker); in prod, set it to your deployed Worker's URL. Same-origin auth
# means the browser sends + receives the session cookie on this Worker's
# domain — no cross-origin cookie config.
VITE_FLARELINK_URL=http://localhost:5174

# --- Server (.dev.vars locally, `wrangler secret put` in prod) ---
# Copy these two lines into a separate file named `.dev.vars` (gitignored).
# They are server-only — `FLARELINK_SERVICE_KEY` must NEVER ship to the
# browser. The Worker uses them to call your Flarelink auth Worker on
# behalf of authenticated users.
#
# Get both from the Flarelink dashboard:
#   1. Provision a project at https://dash.flarelink.dev
#   2. Copy the auth Worker URL → FLARELINK_URL
#   3. Copy the service key (shown once at provision) → FLARELINK_SERVICE_KEY
#
# FLARELINK_URL=https://your-app-auth.your-subdomain.workers.dev
# FLARELINK_SERVICE_KEY=flarelink_sk_...
